Summary: 
 * Merge from SysteMoC--devel--0.9 branch
 - Introduced SimulationCTX
 - SimulationCTX => smoc_simulation_ctx.
   RATIONALE: Lets leave all user visible classes with the SystemC naming
   style. The classes in the Detail namespace will use java style. They should
   not be used by the user anyway. Classes in the SysteMoC namespace should be
   defined by headers in the smoc subdir. The old headers in the systemoc
   subdir will slowly be migrated to the smoc subdir and a dummy header in
   systemoc will pull the class in the SysteMoC namespace defined in the header
   file in the smoc subdir into the global namespace.
 - Moved global variables into smoc_simulation_ctx class. There is still a global var pointing to an
   instance of this class which is access via the SimCTXBase::getSimCTX() method. In the future we
   may eliminate this global var to support diffrent SysteMoC designs in one big simulation.
